{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"neofascist-southmost-caribou","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Why\n\nThe allowlist drain (epic 716f) is removing every entry from `.github/module-size-allowlist.txt`. The FINAL split (reconcile.py) empties the allowlist to zero non-comment entries. That trips a latent bug in the CI `Module-size gate` shell (in both `.github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml` and `.github/workflows/test.yml`): the step runs under `bash -e -o pipefail`, and the line\n\n    listed=$(grep -vE '^[[:space:]]*(#|$)' \"$allowlist\" | awk '{print $1}' | sort -u)\n\nmakes `grep` return exit 1 when the allowlist has NO non-comment lines (no match), which under `pipefail`+`set -e` aborts the whole step with exit 1 BEFORE the over-cap check runs. Confirmed by reproducing locally against the drained tree. Because the gate runs from main's workflow against each change's tree, this fix must land on main BEFORE the allowlist-emptying change (reconcile) can pass Verified.\n\n## What\n\nMake the gate tolerate a zero-entry allowlist (a fully-drained allowlist is a VALID end state). Wrap the grep so a no-match does not abort the step, in BOTH workflow files, keeping behavior identical for a non-empty allowlist:\n\n    listed=$({ grep -vE '^[[:space:]]*(#|$)' \"$allowlist\" || true; } | awk '{print $1}' | sort -u)\n\nBoth workflow files carry the identical gate step (single source of truth, asserted by tests/unit/test_ci_workflow_parity.py), so both must be edited identically.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] In both `.github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml` and `.github/workflows/test.yml`, the Module-size gate's `listed=` line tolerates a no-match grep (does not abort under `set -e`/`pipefail`) (verify: `grep -n 'grep -vE' .github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml .github/workflows/test.yml` shows the guarded form)\n- [ ] Running the gate shell against a zero-entry allowlist exits 0 with 'Module-size gate: OK' (verify: extract the gate step and run it against a comment-only allowlist)\n- [ ] The gate still fails when a non-allow-listed file exceeds 800 LOC (behavior preserved for the non-empty case)\n- [ ] tests/unit/test_ci_workflow_parity.py passes (the two workflow gate steps remain identical)\n\n## Notes\nSmall CI-shell robustness fix; E5 testing-plan is satisfied by the parity test + the manual gate-shell exercise in the AC. This change does NOT modify the allowlist itself (reconcile.py stays listed), so main's current gate passes on it.","id":"da0d-deaf-feb5-4570","parent_id":"716f-b917-9fc8-41f5","priority":1,"tags":["module-size"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Make the module-size gate tolerate a fully-drained (empty) allowlist"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784413074868776001,"uuid":"fe37fb62-80e9-44a9-bf30-003cf23fdab9"}